      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For corners, you should use a specialized corner bead, which is much stronger than just taping. Apply the corner bead firmly in the inside and outside corners, then cover it with a thin layer of mud. When feathering the mud over the bead, make sure you heavily embed the bead into the wet compound. This creates a strong, continuous profile that resists cracking.",
