    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "got it. also, i noticed a couple of tiny gaps or little holes in some of the joints where the boards meet. should i just fill them with the same mud or is there some kind of trick to making sure they don't show up after i paint?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For tiny gaps and pinholes, a small amount of lightweight joint compound is usually sufficient. Instead of just plopping the mud in, use a small putty knife and slightly embed the compound into the void, ensuring you push it right into the opening. After filling, feather the edges out very thinly into the surrounding drywall surface. This smooth transition is what prevents these small imperfections from showing through the final paint coat.",
